<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="552" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,705,1596]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,849,875]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Comparison.</emphasis>
Material compared to 
<taxonomicName box="[629,888,850,876]" class="Ostracoda" family="Podocopida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theriosynoecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvai">
<emphasis box="[629,888,850,876]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Theriosynoecum silvai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, M. D." box="[907,1055,850,876]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="1014 - 1021" refId="ref16679" refString="Silva, M. D. (1978 a) Ostracodes da Formacao Santana (Cretaceo Inferior), Grupo Araripe, Nordeste do Brasil. 1. Novas especies do genero Bisulcocypris. Congresso Brasileiro de Geologia, 30, 1014 - 1021." type="journal article" year="1978">Silva, 1978a</bibRefCitation>
) (Nº DGEO-CTG-UFPE-1970 e DGEO-CTG-UFPE-1166), described and deposited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L." box="[766,971,886,912]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="153 - 176" refId="ref17084" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R., Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L. (2014) Taxonomic studies of non-marine ostracods in the Lower Cretaceous (Aptian-lower Albian) of post-rift sequence from Jatoba and Araripe basins (Northeast Brazil): Stratigraphic implications. Cretaceous Research, 48, 153 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2013.12.007" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tomé 
<emphasis box="[835,891,886,912]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
in the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Ivan de Medeiros Tinoco Microfossils Collection</emphasis>
of the Paleontology Laboratory of the Federal University of 
<collectingRegion box="[1010,1154,922,948]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
. It was observed that the specimen found in the present study corresponds to a juvenile specimen and it has nodules in the posterior margin that differentiate it from the species deposited in the mentioned collection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,705,1596]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,594,1029,1056]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Occurrence and associated fauna</emphasis>
. It was recorded in the Santo Antonio section, just in the depths (from base to top): 
<quantity box="[241,308,1066,1092]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" unit="m" value="0.3">0.3 m</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[320,560,1066,1092]" class="Ostracoda" family="Podocopida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theriosynoecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrinodosum">
<emphasis box="[320,341,1067,1092]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">T.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[384,560,1066,1092]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">quadrinodosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is associated with the species of ostracods: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Krommelbein &amp; Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[1056,1184,1066,1092]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulata">
<emphasis box="[1056,1184,1066,1092]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">P. angulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bate" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[1198,1395,1066,1092]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micropapillosa">
<emphasis box="[1198,1395,1066,1092]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">P. micropapillosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Damonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">D. grandiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[296,323,1103,1128]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">D.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[366,444,1103,1128]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">minuta</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Tomé &amp; Araripe &amp; Oliveira &amp; Barreto &amp; Prado &amp; Pedrosa &amp; Pereira &amp; Nascimento &amp; Ng, 2022" authorityName="Tomé &amp; Araripe &amp; Oliveira &amp; Barreto &amp; Prado &amp; Pedrosa &amp; Pereira &amp; Nascimento &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2022" box="[458,708,1102,1128]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Mantelliana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[458,708,1102,1128]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Mantelliana speculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[714,804,1102,1128]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[714,804,1102,1128]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Tomé &amp; Araripe &amp; Oliveira &amp; Barreto &amp; Prado &amp; Pedrosa &amp; Pereira &amp; Nascimento &amp; Ng, 2022" authorityName="Tomé &amp; Araripe &amp; Oliveira &amp; Barreto &amp; Prado &amp; Pedrosa &amp; Pereira &amp; Nascimento &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2022" box="[858,1158,1102,1128]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Mongolianella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aptianensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[858,1158,1102,1128]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Mongolianella aptianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1165,1254,1102,1128]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1165,1254,1102,1128]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,705,1596]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,358,1137,1163]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Observations</emphasis>
. So far four species belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Branson (1936)" authorityName="Branson" authorityYear="1936" box="[846,1213,1138,1164]" class="Ostracoda" family="Podocopida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theriosynoecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[846,1031,1138,1164]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Theriosynoecum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Branson, C. C." box="[1038,1213,1138,1164]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="323" refId="ref13277" refString="Branson, C. C. (1936) New name for a Morrison ostracode genus. Journal of Paleontology, 10, 323." type="journal article" year="1936">Branson (1936)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
have been recorded in the Aptian/Albian: 
<taxonomicName box="[399,653,1174,1200]" class="Ostracoda" family="Podocopida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theriosynoecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvai">
<emphasis box="[399,653,1174,1200]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Theriosynoecum silvai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, M. D." box="[669,815,1174,1200]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="1014 - 1021" refId="ref16679" refString="Silva, M. D. (1978 a) Ostracodes da Formacao Santana (Cretaceo Inferior), Grupo Araripe, Nordeste do Brasil. 1. Novas especies do genero Bisulcocypris. Congresso Brasileiro de Geologia, 30, 1014 - 1021." type="journal article" year="1978">Silva, 1978a</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Silva" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[837,1105,1174,1200]" class="Ostracoda" family="Podocopida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theriosynoecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="munizi">
<emphasis box="[837,1105,1174,1200]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Theriosynoecum munizi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, M. D." box="[1121,1266,1174,1200]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="1014 - 1021" refId="ref16679" refString="Silva, M. D. (1978 a) Ostracodes da Formacao Santana (Cretaceo Inferior), Grupo Araripe, Nordeste do Brasil. 1. Novas especies do genero Bisulcocypris. Congresso Brasileiro de Geologia, 30, 1014 - 1021." type="journal article" year="1978">Silva, 1978a</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Do Carmo et al., 2013" authorityName="Do Carmo" authorityYear="2013" class="Ostracoda" family="Podocopida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theriosynoecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colini">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Theriosynoecum colini</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Do Carmo, D. A. &amp; Coimbra, J. C. &amp; Whatley, R. C. &amp; Antonietto, L. S. &amp; Citon, R. T. P." box="[280,540,1210,1236]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="91 - 104" refId="ref13960" refString="Do Carmo, D. A., Coimbra, J. C., Whatley, R. C., Antonietto, L. S. &amp; Citon, R. T. P. (2013) Taxonomy of limnic Ostracoda (Crustacea) from the Alagamar Formation, middle-upper Aptian, Potiguar Basin, Northeastern Brazil. Journal of Paleontology, 87, 91 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 11 - 108 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2013">
Do Carmo 
<emphasis box="[409,461,1210,1236]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">et al</emphasis>
., 2013
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Do Carmo et al., 2013" authorityName="Do Carmo" authorityYear="2013" box="[599,1147,1210,1236]" class="Ostracoda" family="Podocopida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theriosynoecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guzzoia">
<emphasis box="[599,879,1210,1236]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Theriosynoecum guzzoia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Do Carmo, D. A. &amp; Coimbra, J. C. &amp; Whatley, R. C. &amp; Antonietto, L. S. &amp; Citon, R. T. P." box="[888,1147,1210,1236]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="91 - 104" refId="ref13960" refString="Do Carmo, D. A., Coimbra, J. C., Whatley, R. C., Antonietto, L. S. &amp; Citon, R. T. P. (2013) Taxonomy of limnic Ostracoda (Crustacea) from the Alagamar Formation, middle-upper Aptian, Potiguar Basin, Northeastern Brazil. Journal of Paleontology, 87, 91 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 11 - 108 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2013">
Do Carmo 
<emphasis box="[1017,1082,1210,1236]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">et al.,</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Regarding the first two, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L." box="[151,360,1246,1272]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="153 - 176" refId="ref17084" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R., Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L. (2014) Taxonomic studies of non-marine ostracods in the Lower Cretaceous (Aptian-lower Albian) of post-rift sequence from Jatoba and Araripe basins (Northeast Brazil): Stratigraphic implications. Cretaceous Research, 48, 153 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2013.12.007" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tomé 
<emphasis box="[222,271,1246,1272]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">et al</emphasis>
. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Silva" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[447,550,1247,1272]" class="Ostracoda" family="Podocopida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theriosynoecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="munizi">
<emphasis box="[447,550,1247,1272]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">T. munizi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in synonymy as being a young form of 
<taxonomicName box="[999,1088,1246,1272]" class="Ostracoda" family="Podocopida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theriosynoecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvai">
<emphasis box="[999,1088,1246,1272]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">T. silvai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen observed in the present manuscript does not resemble the forms found for this interval. However, it corresponds to a young male of 
<taxonomicName box="[181,550,1318,1344]" class="Ostracoda" family="Podocopida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theriosynoecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrinodosum">
<emphasis box="[181,550,1318,1344]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Theriosynoecum quadrinodosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with characteristic nodules in the posterior margin. This species is recorded in interior basins in Northeast 
<collectingCountry box="[460,531,1354,1380]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, of Jurassic age (
<bibRefCitation author="Silva, M. D." box="[719,918,1354,1380]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="1014 - 1021" refId="ref16679" refString="Silva, M. D. (1978 a) Ostracodes da Formacao Santana (Cretaceo Inferior), Grupo Araripe, Nordeste do Brasil. 1. Novas especies do genero Bisulcocypris. Congresso Brasileiro de Geologia, 30, 1014 - 1021." type="journal article" year="1978">
Silva 
<emphasis box="[784,840,1354,1380]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">et al.</emphasis>
1978a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Coimbra, J. C. &amp; Arai, M. &amp; Carreno, A. L." box="[929,1155,1354,1380]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="687 - 698" refId="ref13416" refString="Coimbra, J. C., Arai, M. &amp; Carreno, A. L. (2002) Biostratigraphy of Lower Cretaceous microfossils from the Araripe Basin, northeastern Brazil. Geobios, 35, 687 - 698. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0016 - 6995 (02) 00082 - 7" type="journal article" year="2002">
Coimbra 
<emphasis box="[1033,1089,1354,1380]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">et al.</emphasis>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Guzman-Gonzalez, J. &amp; Sial, A. N. &amp; Piovesan E. K. &amp; Oliveira, E. V. &amp; Fambrini, G. L." pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="113 - 128" refId="ref14258" refString="Guzman-Gonzalez, J., Sial, A. N., Piovesan E. K., Oliveira, E. V. &amp; Fambrini, G. L. (2020) Paleolimnological reconstruction of a marginal area of Jurassic Capianga Lake, Jatoba Basin, northeast Brazil. Journal Paleolimnology, 63, 113 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10933 - 019 - 00105 - 0" type="journal article" year="2020">
Guzmán-González 
<emphasis box="[1381,1437,1354,1380]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
), so if the range of the 
<taxonomicName box="[474,678,1390,1416]" class="Ostracoda" family="Podocopida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theriosynoecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrinodosum">
<emphasis box="[474,678,1390,1416]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">T. quadrinodosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed, it would be recorded as far back as the Aptian. What made the authors leave this species in 
<emphasis box="[587,659,1426,1452]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">confer</emphasis>
is the fact that they found only a single, unique specimen among all the samples.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,705,1596]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,512,1497,1523]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Stratigraphic distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[529,600,1498,1524]" name="Brazil" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, Araripe Basin, Formação, Brejo Santo, Jurassic (
<bibRefCitation author="Coimbra, J. C. &amp; Arai, M. &amp; Carreno, A. L." box="[1183,1425,1498,1524]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="687 - 698" refId="ref13416" refString="Coimbra, J. C., Arai, M. &amp; Carreno, A. L. (2002) Biostratigraphy of Lower Cretaceous microfossils from the Araripe Basin, northeastern Brazil. Geobios, 35, 687 - 698. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0016 - 6995 (02) 00082 - 7" type="journal article" year="2002">
Coimbra 
<emphasis box="[1293,1346,1498,1524]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
). Jatobá Basin, Aliança Formation, Jurassic (
<bibRefCitation author="Guzman-Gonzalez, J. &amp; Sial, A. N. &amp; Piovesan E. K. &amp; Oliveira, E. V. &amp; Fambrini, G. L." box="[644,993,1534,1560]" pageId="17" pageNumber="552" pagination="113 - 128" refId="ref14258" refString="Guzman-Gonzalez, J., Sial, A. N., Piovesan E. K., Oliveira, E. V. &amp; Fambrini, G. L. (2020) Paleolimnological reconstruction of a marginal area of Jurassic Capianga Lake, Jatoba Basin, northeast Brazil. Journal Paleolimnology, 63, 113 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10933 - 019 - 00105 - 0" type="journal article" year="2020">
Guzmán-González 
<emphasis box="[865,924,1534,1560]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="552">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). Araripe Basin, Romualdo Formation, upper Aptian.
</paragraph>
